00:23:04.630 --> 00:23:08.130
about language revitalization
in Cape Breton.

00:23:08.130 --> 00:23:13.580
All these Scotts who arrived
who were 70 years or so,

00:23:13.580 --> 00:23:16.950
many of them were Gaelic speakers
and Gaelic was once the language

00:23:16.950 --> 00:23:19.340
of community life in some
Cape Breton communities

00:23:19.340 --> 00:23:21.590
up through the 1960s or so.

00:23:21.590 --> 00:23:24.940
Some of these places were
primarily Gaelic speaking.

00:23:24.940 --> 00:23:29.220
In 1900 there were 85,000
first language Gaelic speakers

00:23:29.220 --> 00:23:30.520
in Cape Breton.

00:23:30.520 --> 00:23:32.680
Now there are maybe 200, if that.

00:23:32.680 --> 00:23:33.980
There actually was a time

00:23:33.980 --> 00:23:36.890
when Gaelic was Canada's
third most common language,

00:23:36.890 --> 00:23:39.860
most commonly spoken
language, as well.

00:23:39.860 --> 00:23:42.020
And these days we're
seeing a lot of interest

00:23:42.020 --> 00:23:44.870
in language revitalization
in Cape Breton.

00:23:44.870 --> 00:23:46.170
Government programs.

00:23:46.170 --> 00:23:47.470
Local programs.

00:23:47.470 --> 00:23:49.780
Local people teaching
music -- I'm sorry.

00:23:49.780 --> 00:23:51.080
Teaching language.

00:23:51.080 --> 00:23:52.380
And so forth.

00:23:52.380 --> 00:23:56.890
A lot of interest in trying
to bring back the language.

00:23:56.890 --> 00:23:59.910
And when you hear people
talk about language,

00:23:59.910 --> 00:24:02.590
talk about Gaelic language,
they're often talking about music

00:24:02.590 --> 00:24:04.850
in the same breath as
well because music is seen

00:24:04.850 --> 00:24:08.970
as somehow carrying
some of the same values

00:24:08.970 --> 00:24:12.590
that the language carried too,
the same sort of cultural values

00:24:12.590 --> 00:24:15.810
as well, and is seen as
standing for a way of life.

00:24:15.810 --> 00:24:19.340
So we're beginning to see
programs to sort of maintain

00:24:19.340 --> 00:24:21.770
and encourage the language as well.

00:24:21.770 --> 00:24:23.140
By the way, in the French community

00:24:23.140 --> 00:24:26.100
in Cape Breton they've done a great
job bringing the language back

00:24:26.100 --> 00:24:31.200
in the most densely
populated francophone area.

00:24:31.200 --> 00:24:34.620
You can now choose to go to
school in French or in English.

00:24:34.620 --> 00:24:38.450
They raised the funds and
built a community radio station

00:24:38.450 --> 00:24:39.750
